I am guessing that you want unique *id*s.  And you want these prioritized by the tables in some order.  If so, you can do this with `union all` and `row_number()`:

    select id, username, name
    from (select c.*,
                 row_number() over (partition by id order by priority) as seqnum
          from ((select id, username, name, 1 as priority
                 from new_cust
                ) union all
                (select id, username, name, 2 as priority
                 from cust
                ) union all
                (select id, username, name, 3 as priority
                 from old_cust
                )
               ) c
         ) c
    where seqnum = 1;

